      "text": "**Analyzing Navigation Flow**\n\nI'm currently focused on a navigation issue. Clicking \"ENVIAR INVITACIÓN\" or \"enviar un mensaje a la iglesia por WhatsApp\" prevents return to the previous menu. I'm investigating the root cause, focusing on how `App.tsx` handles `currentView`. I'm starting by understanding how this variable dictates the current screen shown, and how a back function can be implemented.\n\n\n**Addressing Navigation Flow**\n\nI've homed in on the `whatsapp` view in `App.tsx`. It looks like the issue stems from the missing \"Back\" functionality within the `WhatsAppMessenger` component. I'm thinking of adding a back button similar to the implementation in the `meeting-detail` view. Also, after a send action, it makes sense to have an option to return automatically. The user highlighted the problem arises *after* a click to send.\n\n\n**Refining Navigation Strategy**\n\nMy focus has shifted to implementing a proper back mechanism for the WhatsApp view. I'm considering storing the \"previous view\" to enable context-aware navigation. I'm also thinking to add a standard \"Back\" button to the WhatsApp view within `App.tsx` and incorporating an `onClose` or `onBack` callback in `WhatsAppMessenger` for better control. I see the importance of ensuring the back button goes to the proper screen.\n\n\n**Implementing Context-Aware Navigation**\n\nI'm now implementing the back button within `App.tsx` directly, aiming for consistency with other views. I'm focusing on making it context-aware, handling the return from the WhatsApp view correctly. I'm also addressing a subtle detail from user feedback: ensuring a seamless return after sending a WhatsApp message. My approach includes storing a \"previousView\" to facilitate this.\n\n\n**Refining Redirection Logic**\n\nI'm now focusing on the post-send redirection within the WhatsApp view. My plan is to add an `onBack` prop to the `WhatsAppMessenger` component and call it following the success alert. Initially, a callback was considered. I'm leaning toward a dedicated \"Volver\" (Return) button at the top of the view. This is preferred over automatically returning as it gives the user more control. I'm exploring how to best manage the `prevView` state to make the return seamless, after the send action completes.\n\n\n",
