      "text": "**Implementing WhatsApp Integration**\n\nI'm focusing on the \"Send Group Invitation\" button, aiming for real functionality within the frontend scope. The current simulation needs replacing. My plan is to implement a \"Send\" flow that leverages WhatsApp's capabilities for group invitations, avoiding complex API integration. This should provide a good user experience.\n\n\n**Refining Send Functionality**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the best method for sending invitations via WhatsApp. Browser security is a key hurdle, so mass tab-opening is out. My plan is to use `window.open` with `https://wa.me/` links. The user wants the \"Send\" button to actually work and have the ability to use the API of their number. This will require generating personalized messages for each leader and constructing the corresponding WhatsApp URL. I'm focusing on modifying `handleBulkWhatsApp` to iterate through the filtered leaders.\n\n\n**Prioritizing User Experience**\n\nI'm now thinking about how to handle multiple WhatsApp links without triggering popup blockers, because the user wants a simple, working \"Group Send\" button. The user's prompt made me think about a \"Click to Send\" queue pattern. My plan is to update `App.tsx` and introduce a \"Bulk Sender\" state, moving from the mass tab-opening idea. I'll add a \"Bulk Sender\" state, and update the UI during the \"Bulk Send\".\n\n\n**Developing Send Queue**\n\nI'm now focusing on generating the WhatsApp links correctly, including phone number formatting. I need to make sure the numbers are in international format. I'm checking `types.ts` and `ChurchManagement.tsx` to confirm the column mapping, confirming `whatsapp` is the source. My plan is to create a phone number cleaning helper and incorporate it into the WhatsApp link generation. I'm currently refining `handleBulkWhatsApp` to iterate through the church data, generate personalized messages, clean phone numbers, and then use `window.open`. The UI is also being updated. I'll implement a \"Send Queue\" overlay to manage the links and provide a better user experience for bulk sending.\n\n\n**Adding Manual Dispatcher**\n\nI'm now integrating a \"Manual Dispatcher\" modal for WhatsApp sending, focusing on a sequential flow as requested. I'll make the \"Group Send\" button trigger the sequential sender using `wa.me`, as it's universally accessible. I'm updating `App.tsx` and refining `handleBulkWhatsApp` to start this queue and implementing a \"WhatsApp Dispatcher\" UI when `isBulkSending` is true. The goal is to provide a user-friendly way to send messages.\n\n\n",
